  "2026-06-12T16:10:43.395Z",maintainer-agent,"Triage complete: 18 open GH issues reconciled. CLOSED AS SHIPPED (verified in /tmp/pm-triage-sandbox on v2026.6.12): GH-153/167/168/170/171/172/174/179/184 (all v2026.6.12) + GH-185 (v2026.6.10). ALREADY TRACKED by open pm items (each references its GH number): GH-154=pm-1lll, GH-155=pm-gcm3, GH-156=pm-j0vc, GH-157=pm-cstl (added Tracks GH-157 comment), GH-158=pm-aer3, GH-161=pm-72xf, GH-163=pm-jmld. NEW: pm-i1z6 for GH-181 remainder (--match-mode and/or/exact + keyword default limit + --count; core no-ranking complaint already fixed by weighted scoring). Quick wins for today: pm-i1z6 default-limit part, pm-cstl --min-score, pm-1lll csv/table, pm-gcm3 child rollup. Leaving this task open for the PR session to close (changelog regen is the last step)."
  "2026-06-12T16:11:30.311Z",maintainer-agent,"Addendum: GH-203 filed mid-triage (validate --check-files classifies existing DIRECTORY links as deleted; prune/auto-fix would remove valid links). Root cause confirmed at src/cli/commands/validate.ts:1287 (!stats.isFile() => missing). Created pm-b1ni (P1, regression of GH-184/pm-0v2m). This is the #1 quick win for today's PR."
  "2026-06-16T11:26:55.094Z",codex-sdk-cli-consolidation-20260616,"Nightly cross-platform regressions hardened: path/url assertions now platform-safe and temp cleanup retries handle transient EBUSY/ENOTEMPTY/EPERM on Windows. Targeted nightly regression subset passes locally (326 tests), plus release/script subset passes (373 tests)."
  "2026-06-16T11:28:52.539Z",codex-sdk-cli-consolidation-20260616,"GitHub reconciliation refresh (2026-06-16): open security/dependency alerts remain 0/0/0; open PR #239 is clean/mergeable. Existing GH->pm mappings confirmed: GH-207->pm-kanu, GH-163->pm-jmld, GH-161->pm-72xf, GH-158->pm-aer3, GH-157->pm-ldr1. Created missing tracker items (no duplicates found via pm search): GH-245->pm-tb42, GH-244->pm-28cf, GH-243->pm-4swf, GH-242->pm-hntj, GH-241->pm-7snq, GH-236->pm-mfl1, GH-235->pm-rpag, GH-217->pm-76r5, GH-216->pm-y1z0, GH-215->pm-u42x, GH-208->pm-52eh, GH-206->pm-mcxr."
